# Adventure POS — Repository rules

Derived from `docs/agent-rules.md`.

## Agent behavior

**Always:** explain major changes before applying; small incremental edits; focused commits; update docs when setup or architecture changes.

**Never:** large refactors without approval; delete modules or directories; silent breaking schema changes; commit secrets or credentials.

## Git workflow

- Work on feature branches only; do not commit directly to `main`.
- Use descriptive messages, e.g. `feat(pos): add line item note support`.

## Documentation

- Update `docs/setup.md` if setup changes.
- Update `README.md` if architecture changes.
- Add module README if module logic becomes complex.

## OpenAI / OpenClaw

- Never store API keys in code; use environment variables only.
- Assume local-only execution unless specified.

## Secrets

- Do NOT store secrets in the repo (use `.env`, not committed).
